---
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
import '../styles/Beep.css';
import beepData from '../data/beepCodes.json';
---
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/STII.png" />
  <title>Motherboard Beep Codes - DOST STII</title>
</head>
<body>
  <Header />

  <div class="beep-wrapper">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <div class="beep-hero">
      <div class="beep-hero-icon">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="48" height="48" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16">
          <path d="M11.5 2a.5.5 0 0 1 .5.5v7a.5.5 0 0 1-1 0v-7a.5.5 0 0 1 .5-.5m2 0a.5.5 0 0 1 .5.5v7a.5.5 0 0 1-1 0v-7a.5.5 0 0 1 .5-.5m-10 8a.5.5 0 0 0 0 1h6a.5.5 0 0 0 0-1zm0 2a.5.5 0 0 0 0 1h6a.5.5 0 0 0 0-1zM5 3a1 1 0 0 0-1 1v4a1 1 0 0 0 1 1h4a1 1 0 0 0 1-1V4a1 1 0 0 0-1-1zm0 1h4v4H5z"/>
          <path d="M0 2a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h12a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v12a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H2a2 2 0 0 1-2-2zm2-1a1 1 0 0 0-1 1v12a1 1 0 0 0 1 1h12a1 1 0 0 0 1-1V2a1 1 0 0 0-1-1z"/>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h1 class="beep-hero-title">Motherboard Beep Code Reference</h1>
        <p class="beep-hero-sub">Diagnose hardware failures using POST (Power-On Self Test) audio signals</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Intro Section -->
    <section class="beep-section">
      <h2 class="beep-heading">WHAT ARE BIOS BEEP CODES?</h2>
      <p>When you turn on a computer, the motherboard performs a procedure called <strong>POST (Power-On Self Test)</strong>, which checks if all essential components are working properly. If a problem is found during this initial verification, the motherboard emits a series of sounds (BEEPs) through the internal speaker.</p>
      <p class="beep-highlight-text">These sounds are not random! They follow specific patterns that indicate which component has a problem. Each BIOS (Basic Input/Output System) manufacturer has its own set of sound codes.</p>

      <div class="beep-callout">
        <strong>Important:</strong> BEEP codes are the first diagnostic tool when a computer cannot complete the boot process to the point of displaying error messages on the screen.
      </div>

      <div class="beep-tags">
        <span class="beep-tag">BIOS</span>
        <span class="beep-tag">POST</span>
        <span class="beep-tag">Diagnostics</span>
        <span class="beep-tag">Hardware</span>
        <span class="beep-tag">Troubleshooting</span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="beep-divider">

    <!-- Why Important -->
    <section class="beep-section">
      <h2 class="beep-heading">Why BEEP Codes are Important</h2>
      <p>BEEP codes are especially useful in the following scenarios:</p>
      <ul class="beep-list">
        <li>The computer cannot fully boot</li>
        <li>There is no display on the screen to show error messages</li>
        <li>You need to diagnose hardware problems quickly</li>
        <li>You are performing maintenance on multiple computers</li>
        <li>A component fails silently without any visible indication</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="beep-components">
        <div class="beep-component-card">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16"><path d="M5 0a.5.5 0 0 1 .5.5V2h1V.5a.5.5 0 0 1 1 0V2h1V.5a.5.5 0 0 1 1 0V2h1V.5a.5.5 0 0 1 1 0V2A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 14 4.5h1.5a.5.5 0 0 1 0 1H14v1h1.5a.5.5 0 0 1 0 1H14v1h1.5a.5.5 0 0 1 0 1H14v1h1.5a.5.5 0 0 1 0 1H14a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-2.5 2.5v1.5a.5.5 0 0 1-1 0V14h-1v1.5a.5.5 0 0 1-1 0V14h-1v1.5a.5.5 0 0 1-1 0V14h-1v1.5a.5.5 0 0 1-1 0V14A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 2 11.5H.5a.5.5 0 0 1 0-1H2v-1H.5a.5.5 0 0 1 0-1H2v-1H.5a.5.5 0 0 1 0-1H2v-1H.5a.5.5 0 0 1 0-1H2A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 4.5 2V.5A.5.5 0 0 1 5 0m-.5 3A1.5 1.5 0 0 0 3 4.5v7A1.5 1.5 0 0 0 4.5 13h7a1.5 1.5 0 0 0 1.5-1.5v-7A1.5 1.5 0 0 0 11.5 3zM5 6.5A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 6.5 5h3A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 11 6.5v3A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 9.5 11h-3A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 5 9.5zM6.5 6a.5.5 0 0 0-.5.5v3a.5.5 0 0 0 .5.5h3a.5.5 0 0 0 .5-.5v-3a.5.5 0 0 0-.5-.5z"/></svg>
          <span>CPU</span>
        </div>
        <div class="beep-component-card">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16"><path d="M4 0a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v1H1a1 1 0 0 0 0 2h1v2H1a1 1 0 0 0 0 2h1v2H1a1 1 0 0 0 0 2h1v1a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h8a2 2 0 0 0 2-2v-1h1a1 1 0 0 0 0-2h-1V9h1a1 1 0 0 0 0-2h-1V5h1a1 1 0 0 0 0-2h-1V2a2 2 0 0 0-2-2zm0 1h8a1 1 0 0 1 1 1v12a1 1 0 0 1-1 1H4a1 1 0 0 1-1-1V2a1 1 0 0 1 1-1"/></svg>
          <span>RAM</span>
        </div>
        <div class="beep-component-card">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16"><path d="M4 8a1.5 1.5 0 1 1 3 0 1.5 1.5 0 0 1-3 0m7.5-1.5a1.5 1.5 0 1 0 0 3 1.5 1.5 0 0 0 0-3"/><path d="M0 1.5A.5.5 0 0 1 .5 1h1a.5.5 0 0 1 .5.5V4h13.5a.5.5 0 0 1 .5.5v7a.5.5 0 0 1-.5.5H2v2.5a.5.5 0 0 1-1 0V2H.5a.5.5 0 0 1-.5-.5m5.5 4a2.5 2.5 0 1 0 0 5 2.5 2.5 0 0 0 0-5M9 8a2.5 2.5 0 1 0 5 0 2.5 2.5 0 0 0-5 0"/><path d="M3 12.5h3.5v1a.5.5 0 0 1-.5.5H3.5a.5.5 0 0 1-.5-.5zm4 1v-1h4v1a.5.5 0 0 1-.5.5h-3a.5.5 0 0 1-.5-.5"/></svg>
          <span>GPU</span>
        </div>
        <div class="beep-component-card">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16"><path d="M11.5 2a.5.5 0 0 1 .5.5v7a.5.5 0 0 1-1 0v-7a.5.5 0 0 1 .5-.5m2 0a.5.5 0 0 1 .5.5v7a.5.5 0 0 1-1 0v-7a.5.5 0 0 1 .5-.5m-10 8a.5.5 0 0 0 0 1h6a.5.5 0 0 0 0-1zm0 2a.5.5 0 0 0 0 1h6a.5.5 0 0 0 0-1zM5 3a1 1 0 0 0-1 1v4a1 1 0 0 0 1 1h4a1 1 0 0 0 1-1V4a1 1 0 0 0-1-1zm0 1h4v4H5z"/><path d="M0 2a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h12a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v12a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H2a2 2 0 0 1-2-2zm2-1a1 1 0 0 0-1 1v12a1 1 0 0 0 1 1h12a1 1 0 0 0 1-1V2a1 1 0 0 0-1-1z"/></svg>
          <span>Motherboard</span>
        </div>
        <div class="beep-component-card">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 16 16"><path d="M14 1a1 1 0 0 1 1 1v8a1 1 0 0 1-1 1H4.414A2 2 0 0 0 3 11.586l-2 2V2a1 1 0 0 1 1-1zM2 0a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v12.793a.5.5 0 0 0 .854.353l2.853-2.853A1 1 0 0 1 4.414 12H14a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V2a2 2 0 0 0-2-2z"/><path d="M3 3.5a.5.5 0 0 1 .5-.5h9a.5.5 0 0 1 0 1h-9a.5.5 0 0 1-.5-.5M3 6a.5.5 0 0 1 .5-.5h9a.5.5 0 0 1 0 1h-9A.5.5 0 0 1 3 6m0 2.5a.5.5 0 0 1 .5-.5h5a.5.5 0 0 1 0 1h-5a.5.5 0 0 1-.5-.5"/></svg>
          <span>BIOS ROM</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="beep-divider">

    <!-- Tabs Navigation -->
    <section class="beep-section">
      <h2 class="beep-heading">Beep Code Reference Tables</h2>
      <p>Select your BIOS manufacturer below. If unsure, check your motherboard manual or look for a logo on the BIOS splash screen at startup.</p>

      <div class="beep-tab-layout">
      <div class="beep-select-wrap">
        <select class="beep-select" onchange="showTab(this.value)">
          {beepData.map(brand => (
            <option value={brand.id}>{brand.label}</option>
          ))}
        </select>
      </div>
      <div class="beep-tab-panes">

      {beepData.map((brand, i) => (
        <div id={`tab-${brand.id}`} class={`beep-tab-content${i === 0 ? ' active' : ''}`}>
          <div class="beep-table-header">
            <strong>{brand.title}</strong>
            <p>{brand.note}</p>
          </div>
          <div class="beep-table-wrap">
            <table class="beep-table">
              <thead><tr><th>{brand.codeHeader}</th><th>Description</th><th>Component</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                {brand.codes.map(c => (
                  <tr>
                    <td>{c.code}</td>
                    <td>{c.desc}</td>
                    <td class={`comp-badge ${c.badge}`}>{c.component}</td>
                  </tr>
                ))}
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}

      </div><!-- end beep-tab-panes -->
      </div><!-- end beep-tab-layout -->
    </section>

    <hr class="beep-divider">

    <!-- Tip Section -->
    <section class="beep-section">
      <h2 class="beep-heading">Troubleshooting Tips</h2>
      <div class="beep-tips-grid">
        <div class="beep-tip-card">
          <div class="beep-tip-num">01</div>
          <h4>Identify your BIOS</h4>
          <p>Check the splash screen when the computer starts, or look at the chip label on the motherboard.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="beep-tip-card">
          <div class="beep-tip-num">02</div>
          <h4>Count the beeps</h4>
          <p>Listen carefully and count each group of beeps. Note any pauses between groups for Phoenix codes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="beep-tip-card">
          <div class="beep-tip-num">03</div>
          <h4>Reseat components</h4>
          <p>For RAM and GPU errors, try removing and firmly reinserting the component before replacing it.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="beep-tip-card">
          <div class="beep-tip-num">04</div>
          <h4>Check connections</h4>
          <p>Loose power cables or improperly seated cards are common causes of POST failures.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    function showTab(name) {
      document.querySelectorAll('.beep-tab-content').forEach(el => el.classList.remove('active'));
      const tab = document.getElementById('tab-' + name);
      if (tab) tab.classList.add('active');
      const sel = document.querySelector('.beep-select');
      if (sel) sel.value = name;
      localStorage.setItem('beep-selected', name);
    }

    (function () {
      const saved = localStorage.getItem('beep-selected');
      if (saved) showTab(saved);
    })();
  </script>

</body>
</html>